<img src="static-images/4stars.gif" alt="4 stars" border="0">
Machine Head is very good album made by Deep Purple with the classic Mk II lineup and of course
the most successful album by Deep Purple ever. Here are three of the most well known Deep Purple's
songs - Highway Star, Smoke on the Water and When a Blind Man Cries. I would like to talk about the
fact that, in spite of being Deep Purple classic this album is not pure hard rock piece, but contains some blues rock elements of the previous release - Fireball! I'm not agree that
Machine Head doesn't contains any progressive elements on it. It contains less than In Rock, but they are still here. They are just lost in all these other
elements. All of the musicians are at the height of their musical abilities and when we combine that
with these immortal songs we get a true ground-breaking album of music as whole!!! 4 stars.</strong></strong></em></em>
</div>




